The '''Tiss'sharl League''' was the governing body of [[Tiss'sharl]]. A consortium of the [[Tiss'shar]] leaders of the five companies that reported the highest profits in the previous five local years,<ref name="GG12">''[[Galaxy Guide 12: Aliens — Enemies and Allies]]''</ref> it consisted of a [[President/Legends|President]] and his [[Vice President/Legends|Vice President]] along with several League Councilors and Officers. It had been established at least since [[1000 BBY/Legends|1000 BBY]].<ref name="Empire 31">[[Empire 31|''Empire'' 31]]</ref>

Around eight months after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], [[Si-Di-Ri]] held the position of [[President of the Tiss'sharl League]], while [[Geor-Dan-Thi]] was Vice-President, having rapidly climbed to that position following the suspicious deaths of [[Mayor/Legends|Mayor]] [[Antha-Kres]], [[Secretary/Legends|Secretary]] [[Lai-O-Sid]], and Vice President [[Astre-De-Kay]]. Following an visit by [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and an [[Assassin/Legends|assassination]] [[Unidentified Tiss'shar assassin|attempt]], Si-Di-Ri resigned, leaving the position open for the ambitious Geor-Dan-Thi.<ref name="Empire 31" />

The successful businessbeing [[San-kur-lor]] was also a constituent of the League.<ref name="GG12" />

